imes been taken as a Welsh equivalent of Latin <i>Theodorus</i>, from Greek <i>Theodōros</i> ‘gift of God’ (see   Theodore  ), for which the usual Welsh form is <i>Tewdwr</i>.","Romanian and Croatian: from the personal name <i>Tudor</i>, a variant of <i>Teodor</i> (see   Theodore  ).","History: The Tudor royal family, English sovereigns from the accession of Henry VII in 1485 to the death of Elizabeth I in 1603, were of Welsh origin, being descended from Owain ap Maredudd ap Tudur, who held lands at Penmynydd in Anglesey."]}]},{"name":"Ithel","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Traditional: compound of <i>iud</i> ‘lord, prince’ + <i>hael</i> ‘generous’; borne in the <i>Mabinogi</i> by the son of Llarian."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Mrs. Ithel ap Tudur was born about 1348, in Llangadwaladr, Denbighshire, Wales. She had at least 1 son with Ithel ap Tudur."},"et":{"about 1348–":"umbes 1348–Surnud","1344–1359":"1344–1359","1374–Male":"1374–Surnud","1348–Female":"1348–Surnud","1348":"1348","1359":"1359","ABT    1374":"umbes 1374","1344":"1344","about 1348":"umbes 1348","1374":"1374","Llangadwaladr, Denbighshire, Wales":"Llangadwaladr, Denbighshire, Wales","of,Llangadwaladr,Anglesey,Wales":"Llangadwaladr, Denbighshire, Wales, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"about 1348–":"noin 1348–Kuollut","1344–1359":"1344–1359","1374–Male":"1374–Kuollut","1348–Female":"1348–Kuollut","1348":"1348","1359":"1359","ABT    1374":"noin 1374","1344":"1344","about 1348":"noin 1348","1374":"1374","Llangadwaladr, Denbighshire, Wales":"Llangadwaladr, Denbighshire, Wales","of,Llangadwaladr,Anglesey,Wales":"Llangadwaladr, Denbighshire, Wales, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"about 1348–":"environ 1348–Décédée","1344–1359":"1344–1359","1374–Male":"1374–Décédé","1348–Female":"1348–Décédée","1348":"1348","1359":"1359","ABT    1374":"environ 1374","1344":"1344","about 1348":"environ 1348","1374":"1374","Llangadwaladr, De